sions. We conclude that planets that open moderately wide and deep gaps\nare subject to the largest torque modifications and their Type II migration can\nbe stalled due to gap edge illumination. We then argue that the torque\nreduction can help to stabilize the orbits of giant planets forming at\n$\\gtrsim$$1$ au.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 29 Sep 2020 16:35:22 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-10-28"}
