 regions with a\nmass variance of 3-4$\\sigma$ at $z\\sim 15-20$ are able to undergo short periods\nof their rapid growth and transits into the Eddington-limited growth phase\nafterwards to be supermassive BHs observed at $z>6-7$.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 30 Sep 2020 13:53:49 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-02-10"}
